er Mason]] (Herbert Millette), [[James Faulkner (actor)|James Faulkner]] (Patrick)\n| ShortSummary    = Suzy and Pat, two struggling actresses, share an apartment together.&nbsp; They get lucky when a millionaire widower invests in their play.&nbsp; Suzy takes advantage and seduces him, but when he asks her to marry him, she is unfaithful.&nbsp; Pat sees a way to take revenge.\n| LineColor       = F1A300\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 31\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1980|11|30|df=y}}\n| Title           = [[Parson's Pleasure (short story)|Parson's Pleasure]]\n| DirectedBy      = [[John Bruce (director)|John Bruce]]\n| WrittenBy       = ''Story by'': Roald Dahl<br>''Dramatisation by'': [[Ronald Harwood]]\n| Aux2            = Roald Dahl\n| Aux3            = [[John Gielgud]] (Cyril Boggis), [[Bernard Miles|The Lord Miles]] (Rummins), [[Lee Montague]] (Storker), [[Godfrey James]] (Claud), [[Irlin Hall]] (Lady), [[Harry Jones (actor)|Harry Jones]] (Bert Rummins), [[Roger Milner]] (Hawkins), [[Virginia Clay]] (Housekeeper)\n| ShortSummary    = A crooked antiques dealer is masquerading as a clergyman.&nbsp; Claiming to be collecting old furniture, he comes across a farmer who gives him an antique piece worth a fortune.\n| LineColor       = F1A300\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 32\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1980|12|7|df=y}}\n| Title           = The Stinker\n| DirectedBy      = [[Alan Gibson (director)|Alan Gibson]]\n| WrittenBy       = ''Story by'': [[Julian Symons]]<br>''Dramatisation by'': [[Julian Bond (writer)|Julian Bond]]\n| Aux2            = \n| Aux3            = [[Colin Hodges]] (Boy), [[Harvey Hillyer]] (Boy), [[David Carlton-Young]] (Boy), [[Robin Keston]] (Boy), [[Russell Gleed]] (Boy), [[Denholm Elliott]] (Colonel Harold Tinker), [[Joss Ackland]] (Jack Cutler), [[Diane Holland]] (Blanche Cutler), [[Tim Bentinck]] (Meech), [[Patricia Quinn]] (Phyl Tinker)\n| ShortSummary    = Millionaire