l]]\n| Aux2            = \n| Aux3            = [[Timothy Carlton]] (Walter Jameson), Gladys Spencer (Old Lady), [[Richard Johnson (actor)|Richard Johnson]] (Parnell), [[Robert Beatty]] (Amos Pulver), [[Victoria Tennant]] (Bernice), [[Vincent Wong (UK actor)|Vincent Wong]] (Japanese Art Collector), [[Michael Forrest]] (Detective Chief Superintendent Nelson), Neil Daglish (Heath), [[Laurence Payne]] (Hollingwood), [[Peter Howell (actor)|Peter Howell]] (Louis Kendall), Olivier Pierre (Andre Arnaud)\n| ShortSummary    = An art gallery owner has received a priceless work of art on loan. He sets up a robbery with a supposed fake being put in its place. He then gets his girlfriend to make a copy of the painting  to sell it as the real thing.\n| LineColor       = F6F8A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 69\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 18\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1982|08|22|df=y}}\n| Title           = The Skeleton Key\n| DirectedBy      = [[Alan Gibson (director)|Alan Gibson]]\n| WrittenBy       = ''Story by'': Graham Sutton<br>''Dramatisation by'': Roy Russell\n| Aux2            = \n| Aux3            = [[Julie Dawn Cole]] (Emma), [[John Duttine]] (Max), [[Peter Jeffrey]] (Stewart), Peter Machin (Andy), [[Tony Osoba]] (Dr Hartley)\n| ShortSummary    = Max, an arrogant young man, plans a holiday with his girlfriend Emma, but he needs an emergency operation beforehand. Andy, a kind-hearted radiologist at the hospital, builds up a friendship with Emma.<br>Max is being very bad tempered,  so she finds she has a decision to make.\n| LineColor       = F6F8A0\n}}\n|}\n\n==Season 6 (1983)==\nFourteen episodes. \n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"width:100%; margin:auto;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background-color: #BFB2B6; color: #ffffff;\" | No. in<br>series\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background-color: #BFB2B6; color: #ffffff;\" | No. in<br>season\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background-color: #BFB2B6; color: #ffffff;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background-