ert Rummins), [[Roger Milner]] (Hawkins), [[Virginia Clay]] (Housekeeper)\n| ShortSummary    = A crooked antiques dealer is masquerading as a clergyman.&nbsp; Claiming to be collecting old furniture, he comes across a farmer who gives him an antique piece worth a fortune.\n| LineColor       = F1A300\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 32\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1980|12|7|df=y}}\n| Title           = The Stinker\n| DirectedBy      = [[Alan Gibson (director)|Alan Gibson]]\n| WrittenBy       = ''Story by'': [[Julian Symons]]<br>''Dramatisation by'': [[Julian Bond (writer)|Julian Bond]]\n| Aux2            = \n| Aux3            = [[Colin Hodges]] (Boy), [[Harvey Hillyer]] (Boy), [[David Carlton-Young]] (Boy), [[Robin Keston]] (Boy), [[Russell Gleed]] (Boy), [[Denholm Elliott]] (Colonel Harold Tinker), [[Joss Ackland]] (Jack Cutler), [[Diane Holland]] (Blanche Cutler), [[Tim Bentinck]] (Meech), [[Patricia Quinn]] (Phyl Tinker)\n| ShortSummary    = Millionaire Jack Cutler runs into Harold Tinker, a boy he used to bully at school.&nbsp; Cutler gives the reluctant Tinker a job.&nbsp; Tinker, however, suspects that Cutler is having an affair with his wife.\n| LineColor       = F1A300\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 33\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1980|12|14|df=y}}\n| Title           = I'll Be Seeing You\n| DirectedBy      = [[Philip Dudley]]\n| WrittenBy       = ''Story by'': [[Robert Quigley]]<br>''Dramatisation by'': Julian Bond\n| Aux2            = \n| Aux3            = [[Robin Marchal]] (Clinker), [[Bryan Andrews (actor)|Bryan Andrews]] (Police Inspector), [[Roger Brierley]] (Jack Parsons), [[Pauline Letts]] (Joan Wilcox), [[Patricia Mort]] (Olive Parsons), [[Alan Foss]] (Hector Wilcox), [[Murray Ewan]] (Professor George Coburn), [[Amanda Redman]] (Anna Warrack), [[Hilary Tindall]] (Vivien Trent), [[Anthony Valentine]] (Roland Trent)\n| ShortSummary    = Roland Trent, husband of a millionairess, is 