or), [[Benjamin Whitrow]] (Fergus Locke), June Watson (Audrey Locke), [[Fanny Rowe]] (Actress), Angela Harding (Cathleen) \n| ShortSummary    = Two old actor friends meet up for the first time in 25 years. They ponder the fact that neither of them has been successful in his career or life, and reminisce about a girl on whom they both had a crush.\n| LineColor       = F6F8A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 65\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 14\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1982|07|25|df=y}}\n| Title           = The Absence of Emily\n| DirectedBy      = [[Alan Gibson (director)|Alan Gibson]]<br>John Rosenberg\n| WrittenBy       = ''Story by'': [[Jack Ritchie]]<br>''Dramatisation by'': [[Denis Cannan]]\n| Aux2            = \n| Aux3            = [[Anthony Valentine]] (Bob), [[Frances Tomelty]] (Norma), Susan Tracy (Emily), [[Patsy Byrne]] (Jean), [[Patrick McAlinney]] (Landlord), [[William Moore (actor)|William Moore]] (Crisp), Derek Anders (Goff), [[Diana King (actress)|Diana King]] (Ruth)\n| ShortSummary    = Norma has inherited a large estate and allows her sister Emily and brother-in-law Bob to live there.<br>Emily disappears and Norma believes that Bob has killed her for an insurance pay out. A detective and she investigate.\n| LineColor       = F6F8A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 66\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 15\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1982|08|01|df=y}}\n| Title           = In the Bag\n| DirectedBy      = Bert Salzman\n| WrittenBy       = ''Story by'': Robert L. Fish<br>''Dramatization by'': [[Bert Salzman]]\n| Aux2            = \n| Aux3            = [[Edward Albert]] (Sam), [[Terry O'Quinn]] (Cop), [[Lou Jacobi]] (Waiter), [[Roxanne Hart]] (Cara), Michael A. Candela (Gardener) \n| ShortSummary    = Cara is determined to get back her family jewels, which have been hidden away in a safe. Hiring a safe cracker, she goes along with him undercover.\n| LineColor       = F6F8A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 67\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 16\n| Orig