er), [[Samantha Eggar]] (Gwen Carter), [[Denise Galik]] (Melanie Todd)\n| ShortSummary    = Reeve Baker is a successful romantic novelist.&nbsp; Gwen, the wife of a friend, falls for Baker, and despite her husband's warnings, carries on with the relationship.\n| LineColor       = EDC155\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 100\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1985|07|14|df=y}}\n| Title           = In the Cards\n| DirectedBy      = [[John Peyser]]\n| WrittenBy       = ''Story by'': John Collier<br>''Dramatisation by'': Ross Thomas & [[A.&nbsp;A. Roberts]]\n| Aux2            = <!--NOTE: IMDb says [[Roald Dahl]] introduced this episode, while http://www.talesoftheunexpectedtvseries.co.uk/ says that Dahl never introduced any episodes past \"Parson's Pleasure\" (S3E6)-->\n| Aux3            = [[Kenneth Tigar]] (Merrifield), [[Elaine Giftos]] (Grace), [[Susan Strasberg]] (Madame Myra), [[Max Gail]] (Charlie)\n| ShortSummary    = Madame Myra is a fortuneteller with a lacklustre career and dim future.&nbsp; A man shows up eventually who is eager to guide her to a better life, but he has an ulterior motive.\n| LineColor       = EDC155\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 101\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|1985|07|21|df=y}}\n| Title           = Nothin' Short of Highway Robbery\n| DirectedBy      = [[John Peyser]]\n| WrittenBy       = ''Story by'': [[Lawrence Block]]<br>''Dramatisation by'': [[Luther Murdoch]]\n| Aux2            = <!--NOTE: IMDb says [[Roald Dahl]] introduced this episode, while http://www.talesoftheunexpectedtvseries.co.uk/ says that Dahl never introduced any episodes past \"Parson's Pleasure\" (S3E6)-->\n| Aux3            = [[Jennifer Holmes (actress)|Jennifer Holmes]] (Marcie), [[Bud Cort]] (Newt), [[Bettye Ackerman]] (Ruby), [[Warren Oates]] (Harry)\n| ShortSummary    = A husband and wife are embarking on a long drive through the desert.&nbsp; They stop off at a rundown gas station to be told that th